{"id": 6064, "title": "Ticket #6064: Negotiator crashes on Ubuntu 16", "description": "<blockquote>\nUbuntu 16 has the new implementation of std::string, which uses the Short String Optimization (SSO).  With this change, it is no longer valid to memcpy std:string objects (which we shouldn't have been doing in first place).  However, the negotiator did keep an array of std::string's by value, which we then qsort'ed in place, causing a crash on newer gcc-compiled condors.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Jan-18 10:10:26 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW:</strong> Nice simple code change to avoid the crash.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Jan-20 10:52:24 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\nNever released on Ubuntu 16. So, no docs needed.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Jan-20 13:39</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/4536308096aaea2a297f895b739ac7f9ae43b6d6\">[50029]</a></span>: Got ticket number wrong <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6054\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6054'); return false;\" title=\"condor_status print format config behaves oddly with -af\">#6054</a></span> -&gt; <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=6064\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6064'); return false;\" title=\"Negotiator crashes on Ubuntu 16\">#6064</a></span>  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Dec-20 22:36</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"to